Dreamon21
Hong Kong, China62 contributions
3.0 of 5 bubbles
My Khe during Tet
Feb 2024 • Family
From our hotel rooftop pool and bar we can see My Khe. The view is stunning but with strong waves obviously not suitable for swimming. We decided to step onto the beach on this windy and wintery day. It was peaceful and rather empty because it was Tet. We didn't encounter any touts maybe it was Tet and the people were on Tet holiday reunion back home. There are a few massage huts still operating during Tet along the beach. There are "No Swimming" signs on the beach. The waves are indeed strong and at times look like mini tsunamis. I stood on dry beach to take a photo but when I looked into my phone camera and shot in a second my shoes and pants were already soaked by the waves, yikes! Obviously no swimming for anyone unless you are a pro surfer. While we were there during Tet week, it was too cloudy, windy and wintery to do any beach activities except for a stroll. Since the place wasn't busy for a while, we didn't see much rubbish like the rest of Vietnam. Having a short stroll at the beach was sufficient. You do not want to do anything else that could hurt you including massages that don't look very hygenic.
Written February 19, 2024
This review is the subjective opinion of a Tripadvisor member and not of Tripadvisor LLC. Tripadvisor performs checks on reviews as part of our industry-leading trust & safety standards. Read our transparency report to learn more.
