We'd been told this was the best beach in Vietnam - hard to believe
Mar 2020
I haven't seen them all, and to be fair it's a long strip of soft sand. The waves crash to shore which could make swimming difficult for anyone less than very steady on their feet. Sunbeds and brellas are tired but cheap. My biggest gripe was that the sand is littered with cigarette butts and other small pieces of rubbish. Sunbeds are shorter than any I've experienced elsewhere. Maybe I missed the best part, but An Bang 20 minutes south was a better locations for me, with beach bars backing the beach which was cleaner and just as soft sand....
